<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Code of Ethics</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Taslow">Taslow</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:41 a.m. 6/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Code of Ethics<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/mithaniel_marr.cgi?read=29" TARGET=_self>Code of Ethics</A> (GMoney)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I do not understand why you had to change you name in the first place. As you said, this
<BR>is you fantasy game and as long as your not being obsence or using profanity, we should
<BR>be allow to use the names we wish!
<P>&gt; First let me apologize for the message I
<BR>&gt; posted regarding my name. If I offended
<BR>&gt; anyone I am very sorry. I suppose that in
<BR>&gt; the struggle for EverQuest to establish
<BR>&gt; itself a chokehold of conformity has
<BR>&gt; threaded its way into Norrath. 'Tis a shame
<BR>&gt; but inevitable I suppose. I have a strict
<BR>&gt; moral code in real life as well as in my
<BR>&gt; fantasy role playing. That is my point. This
<BR>&gt; is my fantasy...I am the one paying the
<BR>&gt; bills to play this game. I feel that freedom
<BR>&gt; of expression comes in all forms. I have
<BR>&gt; seen many names in our wonderful game.
<BR>&gt; Everyone accepts those fit into their idea
<BR>&gt; of what EQ should be. Even as you scroll
<BR>&gt; down the message board you can see the
<BR>&gt; obvious variety. Each name is someone
<BR>&gt; fulfilling their fantasy, regardless of how
<BR>&gt; ridiculous it appears to the next player.
<BR>&gt; The only reason I chose my name again was so
<BR>&gt; that when players who knew me knew they were
<BR>&gt; protected to the best of my abilities, as
<BR>&gt; long as they hadn't brought rath through
<BR>&gt; dishonorable actions. I would gladly lay
<BR>&gt; down my life for anyone whose path I
<BR>&gt; crossed, irregardless of their names, or
<BR>&gt; their deity, or their race.
<BR>&gt; However this is all a moot point because I
<BR>&gt; am bowing to the conformity and changing a
<BR>&gt; name that has been mine for a decade. Truly
<BR>&gt; this is a sad passage for me. The moral code
<BR>&gt; of ethics I am so proud to have nutured over
<BR>&gt; many, many years tells me I should not back
<BR>&gt; down, that I should stand for what I know is
<BR>&gt; right. Instead, for the honor of my guild
<BR>&gt; and everyone's peace of mind I am willingly
<BR>&gt; changing my name. It has been painful to be
<BR>&gt; taunted when I never meant harm. With a
<BR>&gt; heavy heart I resign my name. Perhaps now I
<BR>&gt; can get back to doing what I do best-beating
<BR>&gt; the crap out of bad things. If you meet me
<BR>&gt; on the path do not hesitate to ask for
<BR>&gt; anything you might need, I will cheerfully
<BR>&gt; do my best to help. But please, I beg you,
<BR>&gt; do not insult my honor, because I would
<BR>&gt; never insult yours. Thank you for listening,
<BR>&gt; safe hunting and may the Light of Marr shine
<BR>&gt; on you all.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
